<div id="Item_0" class="PageTitle"><div class="Options"></div><h1>Promotion (Stephen J. Taylor)</h1></div>

<div id="Discussion_36825" class="Item ItemDiscussion">
    <div class="Discussion">
        <div class="Item-Header DiscussionHeader">
            <div class="AuthorWrap">
            <span class="Author">
                <a title="T5 Saunders" href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T5%20Saunders" class="PhotoWrap"><img src="../../uploads/userpics/773/nRHKODQ2CR8WX.jpg" alt="T5 Saunders" class="ProfilePhoto ProfilePhotoMedium" /></a><a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T5%20Saunders" class="Username">T5 Saunders</a>            </span>
            <span class="AuthorInfo">
                            </span>
            </div>
            <div class="Meta DiscussionMeta">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
                <a href="promotion-stephen-j-taylor" class="Permalink" rel="nofollow"><time title="April 6, 2020 4:47AM" datetime="2020-04-06T04:47:43+00:00">April 2020</time></a>            </span>
                                 <span class="MItem Category"> in <a href="../../categories/promotions-and-awards">Promotions and Awards</a></span>             </div>
        </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
            <div class="Item-Body">
                <div class="Message userContent">
                    <p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://personnel.29th.org/#members/88151">Sgt. Mellinger</a> said:</p>

<blockquote class="UserQuote"><div class="QuoteText">
  <p>Before ending up in Easy Company, <a rel="nofollow" href="http://personnel.29th.org/#members/88842">Pvt. Taylor</a> had some service time in Dog Company. He was there for over six months but, he never made it to PFC before he had to discharge for a bit. Fast forward to today, Pvt. Taylor has shown up in EP4S2 and has shown only excellence. He's got perfect attendance, a great attitude, and performs exceptionally well in drills for only being here for a month. I honestly can't think of anything negative to put on this guy. In only a month, he has impressed his squad leadership, platoon leadership, and people outside of our squad. Since he has been doing so well and has been here for quite some time now, his Squad Leadership and Platoon HQ believe he has earned a promotion to the rank of Private, First Class. Keep up the excellent work PFC Taylor.</p>
</div></blockquote>

<hr />

<p></p><div style="text-align: center;">

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealheaderblack.png" alt="" title="" /></p>

<p>CERTIFICATION OF PROMOTION</p>

<p><b>TO ALL WHO SHALL SEE THESE PRESENTS, GREETING:</b></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Know Ye, that reposing special trust and<br /> confidence in the fidelity and abilities of</span></p>

<p><code><a rel="nofollow" href="http://personnel.29th.org/#members/88842">Stephen J. Taylor</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 168563212&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; EP4S2</code></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">I do promote him to <u>Private, First Class</u> in the </span></p>

<p><span style="font-size: xx-large;">UNITED STATES ARMY</span></p>

<p>to rank as such from the <u> 5th </u> day of <u> April 2020 </u>.</p>

<p>You are charged to discharge carefully and diligently the duties of the grade to which promoted and to uphold the traditions and standards of the Army.</p>

<p>Effective with this promotion you are charged to execute diligently your special skills with a high degree of technical proficiency and to maintain standards of performance, moral courage and dedication to the Army which will serve as outstanding examples to your fellow soldiers. You are charged to observe and follow the orders and directions given by superiors acting according to the law, articles and rules governing the discipline of the Army. Your unfailing trust in superiors and loyalty to your peers will significantly contribute to the readiness and honor of the United States Army.</p>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealfooter.png" alt="" /></p>

<p></p></div>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/LTC_Wheatley.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<hr />
